-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/citigroup-hires-ubs-s-palamara-for-high-yield-distressed-sales.html
Citigroup Inc. (C)  said it hired Frank Palamara from UBS AG for high-yield and distressed debt sales.  Palamara is rejoining Citigroup after leaving in 2009 to be
a senior salesman covering high-yield and leveraged loan markets
at UBS, the New York-based bank said in a statement today.
Citigroup also said Nathan Stone is joining its high-yield team
from London-based Evolution Securities Ltd.  Stone and Palamara start next month in London and will
report to Conor Davis, head of credit sales for Citigroup in
 Europe , according to the statement.  Citigroup is the fifth-largest manager of high-yield bond
sales worldwide this year, accounting for 8.3 percent of the
$242 billion of total issuance, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
